    "body": "### Problem\n\nI noticed that neovim does not remove inlay hints when there is only one inlay hint in a file.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nConfig:\n\n```lua\nlocal pattern = 'go'\nlocal cmd = {'gopls'}\nlocal root_markers = {'go.mod', '.git'}\nlocal settings = {\n\tgopls = {\n\t\thints = {\n\t\t\tignoredError = true,\n\t\t},\n\t},\n}\n\nlocal capabilities = vim.lsp.protocol.make_client_capabilities()\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\n\tpattern = pattern,\n\tcallback = function(args)\n\t\tlocal match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\n\t\tlocal root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, ':p:h') or nil\n\t\tvim.lsp.start({\n\t\t\tname = 'gopls',\n\t\t\tcmd = cmd,\n\t\t\troot_dir = root_dir,\n\t\t\tsettings = settings,\n\t\t\tcapabilities = capabilities,\n\t\t})\n\tend\n})\n\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('LspAttach', {\n\tdesc = 'Enable inlay hints',\n\tcallback = function(event)\n\t\tvim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable(true, {bufnr = event.buf})\n\tend,\n})\n```\n\nGo source:\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport \"os\"\n\nfunc main() {\n\tos.Open()\n}\n```\n\nAt the `os.Open()` line in normal mode do a `dd`. Inlay hint does not disappear.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nInlay hint should disappear.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.3\n\n### Language server name/version\n\ngopls v0.20\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Workaround:\n\n```lua\n-- Workaround for https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/35110\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"TextChanged\", \"TextChangedI\", \"BufEnter\" }, {\n\tcallback = function(args)\n\t\tlocal bufnr = args.buf\n\t\tif vim.lsp.inlay_hint.is_enabled({bufnr = bufnr}) then\n\t\t\tvim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable(false, {bufnr = bufnr})\n\t\t\tvim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable(true, {bufnr = bufnr})\n\t\tend\n\tend,\n})\n```",
